  "doc_id": "31847",
  "text": "Note that the algebra R g,0 (W ) is isomorphic to the subalgebra R g (W ) of the rational Cherednik algebra H g (W ) given as R g (W ) = ρ(R g,0 (W )). Furthermore, the central quotient R g,0 (W )/(H + 1) is a flat family of non-homogeneous quadratic Poincaré-Birkhoff-Witt algebras in the sense of [CITATION_1] . Indeed, let us consider the central quotient of the algebra H N,N +1 w, where w ∈ W , i rs ∈ N ∪ {0}, i N,N +1 ≤ 1, and monomials have no crossings. It is also clear that all the defining relations of the algebra R g,0 (W )/(H + 1) are quadratic.",
